SIMPLE: prevention
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prevention
<hw>Pre*ven"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧vention</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of going,
or state of being, before.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The greater the distance, the greater the
<qex>prevention</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anticipation; esp., anticipation of needs or wishes;
hence, precaution; forethought.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hammond. Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act of preventing or hindering; obstruction of
action, access, or approach; thwarting.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Casca, be sudden, for we fear <qex>prevention</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Prejudice; prepossession.</def> <mark>[A
Gallicism]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preventional</ent>⟦br⟧
